name: Epic Games
summary: The Epic Games Store has expanded to mobile devices, offering users an alternative app marketplace on both iOS and Android platforms. This move comes amidst an ongoing legal battle between Epic Games and Apple over Apple's strict control of the iOS App Store. In a related move, Fortnite, Epic Games' popular battle royale game, has returned to Apple devices in Europe after being removed in 2020 due to the same legal dispute. The game is also now available globally on Android devices through the Epic Games Store. Meanwhile, in a separate development, Epic Games has made the EU-based alternative app store, AltStore, available for free through its MegaGrant program, providing users with another option for accessing apps outside of the official App Store.

name: Post Malone
summary: Post Malone's long-anticipated country album, "F-1 Trillion," has finally been released to critical acclaim. Critics have praised the album's unique sound and Malone's heartfelt lyrics, which explore themes of loneliness, success, and his relationship with his daughter. The album features collaborations with numerous artists, including The Kid LAROI, Dolly Parton, and Fleet Foxes. In interviews, Malone has discussed the personal struggles he faced in recent years, including loneliness and depression. He credits his daughter with saving his life and inspiring him to make music that connects with his audience. Malone has ranked his favorite tracks on the album, with "Love/Hate Letter to Alcohol" topping the list. The album's release has been celebrated with a special performance at the Outside Lands festival in San Francisco, and Malone has expressed his preference for the Nashville music scene over Los Angeles, which he feels is more demanding and less genuine.

summary: Marvel has fired Beau DeMayo, the creator of the animated series "X-Men '97," for "egregious" misconduct. The investigation found "egregious" behavior on DeMayo's part, but Marvel has not disclosed the specific nature of the misconduct. DeMayo has denied any wrongdoing and claims that he was fired in retaliation for his support of LGBTQIA+ rights. Marvel has also denied DeMayo's claim that he was denied credit for his work on Season 2, saying that he is still credited as the creator of the series.

name: Victoria Jackson
summary: Former "Saturday Night Live" cast member Victoria Jackson has revealed that her cancer has returned, and she now has an inoperable tumor in her windpipe. The 65-year-old comedian shared the news in a post on social media, saying that she has been given a prognosis of less than three years to live. Jackson says she is determined to live life to the fullest despite her diagnosis and has expressed gratitude for the support she has received from her fans.

summary: UFC 307, set to take place in Salt Lake City, has announced its official main card. The highly anticipated event will feature Alex Pereira, the current middleweight champion, defending his title against Khalil Rountree. Additionally, Raquel Pennington will face Julianna Peńa in a women's bantamweight bout. UFC President Dana White confirmed these matchups, along with several other exciting fights, including Cory Sandhagen vs. Marlon Vera and Sean Brady vs. Michael Chiesa. Fans can expect an electrifying night of MMA action with Pereira-Rountree serving as the main attraction.
